JOHANNESBURG - The Constitutional Court wants answers from the Social Development Minister and Sassa.It's instructed Minister Bathabile Dlamini and the social security agency to explain why they missed Monday's deadline.READ: Gordhan confident grants will be paid on 1 AprilThe court had ordered that they explain why they had failed to prepare to take over the distribution of social grants from April.They were late to file the papers -- submitting them after 10pm -- instead of 4pm as per the court's instruction.The papers were also meant to respond to the court's questions on the legality of a new deal with CPS.The minister and Sassa have until 3pm this afternoon to file their affidavits.eNCA